The '''''International Wood Products Journal''''' (print: {{ISSN|2042-6445}}, on-line: {{ISSN|2042-6453}}), formerly ''The Journal of the Institute of Wood Science'' ({{ISSN|0020-3203}}), is published by [[Maney Publishing]] on behalf of [[The Wood Technology Society]] of the [[Institute of Materials, Minerals and Mining]]. It is a biannual, [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[scientific journal]] covering all aspects of wood science, engineering, and technology, its processing and applications. It obtained its new name in 2010 and is edited by [[Gervais Sawyer]].

The main subject areas include properties of [[wood]], testing and characterisation, drying, wood protection, processing and machining, structural applications, products and applications, recycling, wood modification, life cycle assessment, [[carbon sequestration]], logistics, economics, environmental impacts and any other topics of interest to those involved in wood. The journal accepts papers, technical notes, reviews, and case studies.

